<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>
<head>
<title>REPLACE-DEAD-AGENT</title>

</head>
<body>
	<h3><i>I replace myself when dying by creating a new replacement agent.</i>

	</h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>REPLACE-DEAD-AGENT</b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>when [dead]
     [add-copies 1 list-of-micro-behaviours "Replacement Behaviours" [INITIALISE-AGENT.html SET-RANDOM-UNOCCUPIED-POSITION.html REPLACE-DEAD-AGENT.html]]</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>


	<p><i>dead</i> is set by

	<a title="DIE" href="DIE.html">DIE</a> 

	which is run by

	<a title="DIE-IF-NO-SUGAR" href="DIE-IF-NO-SUGAR.html">

	DIE-IF-NO-SUGAR</a> and

	<a title="DIE-IF-TOO-OLD" href="DIE-IF-TOO-OLD.html">

	DIE-IF-TOO-OLD</a>. This relies upon

	<a title="INITIALISE-AGENT" href="INITIALISE-AGENT.html">

	INITIALISE-AGENT</a> and

	<a title="SET-RANDOM-UNOCCUPIED-POSITION" href="SET-RANDOM-UNOCCUPIED-POSITION.html">

	SET-RANDOM-UNOCCUPIED-POSITION</a>.</p>

	<h2>Source</h2>
	<p>Based upon page 32 of [1].</p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>When <i>dead</i> is TRUE then this rule will be run before I'm removed 

	from the model. It creates a copy of myself except for the effects of

	<a title="INITIALISE-AGENT" href="INITIALISE-AGENT.html">

	INITIALISE-AGENT</a> and

	<a title="SET-RANDOM-UNOCCUPIED-POSITION" href="SET-RANDOM-UNOCCUPIED-POSITION.html">

	SET-RANDOM-UNOCCUPIED-POSITION</a>. The newly created copy also needs this 

	rule and hence is included in the list of micro-behaviours.</p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn.</p>

	<h2>References</h2>

	<p>[1] <i>Growing Artificial Societies</i> by Joshua M. Epstein and Robert 

	Axtell, Brookings Institute Press, The MIT Press, 1996.</p>

